The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Business Briefs

 New Delhi, April 3: The government today reconstituted the board of trade with AV Birla group chief Kumar Mangalam Birla as its chairman and Maruti Udyog chief Jagdish Khattar and Baba Kalyani of Bharat Forge among its 38 members. The board has been reconstituted by commerce and industry minister Kamal Nath with effect from April 1 in order to ?ensure a continuous dialogue with trade and industry?, an official release said. It would inter-alia advise the government on policy measures connected with the foreign trade policy. 

 New Delhi, April 3: The CII-Ascon survey has reported that diesel, petrol, edible oils and rubber footwear are among the 34 sectors which registered more than 34 per cent growth in the country?s manufacturing sector, while cast iron, spun pipe, polyester and sponge-iron recorded a negative growth last fiscal.

 New Delhi, April 3: Mahanagar Telecom Nigam Ltd (MTNL) will start the voluntary retirement scheme for 8000-strong group-B staff this fiscal.

 New Delhi, April 3: Worldwide business process outsourcing (BPO) market is expected to grow 8 per cent in 2005 to $133.7 billion and the rising demand will create a sellers market, according to research firm Gartner.

 Kuwait City, April 3: The president of the Organization of Petroleum Exporting Countries, Sheikh Ahmad Fahad Al-Ahmad Al-Sabah, has said the group will increase its production ceiling by 500,000 barrels a day starting in May.




